Installation Steps:

Step1: Download the "videorecorder".

Step2: Upload the "videorecorder" directory into your "webapps" directory of your red5 installation. Dont change the directory name and keep it "videorecorder".

Step3: Open the file js/recorder.js. Change the flash variables like "server", "filename", "av_mode" with the exact server location, suitable file names and different mode like audio/ video / default [For default do not use this variable].

Step4: Open the index.html file into your browser and start recording. It can be any file name.

Step5: After finish click on stop. automatically you will get one .flv file generated under the directory "Streams". The file name by default "recorded_audio.flv". You can change it from the recorder.js